title: Mingus boys place 10th in Titan Invitational
text: Dan Engler Editor GILBERT - Fueled by a fourth-place finish by senior Joseph Sandoval, the Mingus boys cross country team finished 10th out of 21 teams in the 2nd annual Titan Invitational at Crossroads Park here Friday.The invitational was hosted by Chandler Preparatory Academy.Sandoval covered the 5-kilometer course in 17:43, just 31 seconds off the winning pace established by junior Travor Tam of Horizons Honor High School.Mingus other scoring runners finished in the 40 (junior Ryan Alexander, 19:31), 44 (senior Cristian Lazaro, 19:41), 84 (junior Justin Stuart, 21:09) and 91 Junior Tyler Lewis, 21:53) scoring positions.The Mingus girls did not field a full team.Senior Megan Goettl was 17th in a field of 118 runners with a time of 22:51 over 3.1 miles. Junior Rachel Valentine was 69th in 26:58. Sophomore Hannah DeVore was 71st in 27:10.
